        </MudListItem>

        <MudListItem>
            <strong>Source Code</strong>: GitHub -> <strong>unavailable</strong>, the project consists of private tokens; the source code can be shown if requested
        </MudListItem>

        <MudListItem>
            <strong>Main Aim</strong>: Provide Arma 3 (video game) players ability to check the ban status of other players
        </MudListItem>

        <MudListItem>
            <strong>Usage</strong>: Google Analytics collects the usage data; the Web application currently has nearly 250 registered users
        </MudListItem>

        <MudListItem>
            <strong>Pictures</strong>: The main page (after SteamId authentication) can be seen <MudLink Href="icons/cbc.png" Target="_blank">here</MudLink>; 
            check service can be seen <MudLink Href="icons/cbccheck.png" Target="_blank">here</MudLink>
        </MudListItem>
    </MudList>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">
        Description:<br/>
        Coke's Ban Checker is one of the most advanced project in my portfolio. It has the following features:

        <MudList>
            <MudListItem>
                <strong>OpenId authentication for Steam</strong>: Users are required to authenticate their SteamId in order to use the website
            </MudListItem>

            <MudListItem>
                <strong>Database</strong>: PostgreSQL
            </MudListItem>

            <MudListItem>
                <strong>Database mapper</strong>: Entity Framework Core
            </MudListItem>

            <MudListItem>
                <strong>API</strong>: Users can create their own JWT Web Token in order to use the API which services are connected to. Furthermore, users can learn API endpoints through the Swagger documentation
            </MudListItem>

            <MudListItem>
                <strong>Roles</strong>: Each user has their own role, depending on the role s/he can use and see different pages. The user who possesses admin role can change users' roles through the Web application
            </MudListItem>
        </MudList>
    </MudText>

